This shell scripts are designed to allow some basic MySQL administration operations to be done easily. It is distributed under GNU/GPL v2 licence so use it at you own risks.

# Config
Set the config path in the credentials.sh file. And do : echo "root password" > database in the config folder.

# Scripts
setdatabasecollate.sh : Turn a complete database collation to UTF8
createuser.sh : Create a new mysql user
createdatabase.sh : Create a new mysql database and give rights to a user if given
dumpdatabase.sh : Dump the given database to the given file
mountdatabase.sh : Mount the given database from the given file
credentials.sh : Do not use it

# Modify
I you improve those scripts, please, pull your commits !